g.data-name: June 2020 TiDB Cloud beta was launched
May 2019 TiKV was voted to be a CNCF Incubating project
November 2018 TiDB Cloud was open for testing on Google Cloud Platform GCP
August 2018 - TiDB Operator was open sourced - CNCF accepted TiKV as a Sandbox project
June 2017 Received 15M series B funding from Huachuang Capital
August 2016 - Received series A funding with Yunqi Capital - Landed the first in-production adopter
April 2016 TiKV the distributed KV storage engine based on Google Spanner was open sourced
September 2015 TiDB was open sourced on GitHub
April 2015 PingCAP was founded with the angel round funding finished
Sep 2020 CNCF announced TiKV to be a Graduated project
July 2020 CNCF accepted Chaos Mesh as a Sandbox project
